 **Answer:** To find the average (arithmetic mean) age of the Ninja Turtles, we first add up all their ages and then divide by the number of turtles.

In mathematics, this operation is often represented by the formula for the arithmetic mean (average). In this case:

<box>
\begin{equation*}
\text{{Average Age}} = \frac{\sum_\text{{Age}}}{\text{{Number of Turtles}}}
= \frac{2*(15)+2*(17)}{4}
= \frac{60}{4}
= 15
\end{equation*}
</box>

So, the average age of the Ninja Turtles is 15 years. Keep in mind that this answer represents a theoretical mean age as we can only consider whole numbers for the ages of our Ninja Turtles. In reality, each turtle may have a slightly different age due to slight differences in incubation periods or other factors.

